250 g Ground Turkey
¾ cup Basmati Rice
4 g Cumin-Turmeric Spice Blend
1 tbsp Garlic Puree
6 tbsp Yogurt Sauce
113 g Mirepoix
10 g Indian Spice Mix
7 g Cilantro
28 g Crispy Shallots
56 g Green Peas
2 tbsp Curry Paste
2 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Using a strainer, rinse rice until water runs clear.
Add rice, garlic puree and peas to the pot of boiling water. Cover and reduce heat to low. Cook for 12-15 min, until rice is tender and water is absorbed. Remove from heat. Set aside, still covered.

Meanwhile, heat a large non-stick pan over high. When the pan is hot, add turkey, mirepoix and Indian Spice Mix to dry pan. Cook for 2-4 min, breaking up turkey into smaller pieces, until no pink remains.**  Season with salt and pepper.
Add curry paste and 1/2 cup (1 cup) water. Cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened, 1-2 min. Remove the pan from heat.

Meanwhile, to a small microwavable bowl, add 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) butter and Cumin-Turmeric Spice Blend. Microwave in 30-sec increments until butter is melted. Stir to comine.

Fluff rice with a fork, then pour melted butter mixture over top.
Divide rice between plates.
Top with turkey mixture.
Tear cilantro and sprinkle crispy shallots over top.
Drizzle yogurt sauce over top.

If you've opted to get turkey, cook in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the beef.** Disregard instructions to drain excess fat.